sentences: Ithamara Koorax (born 23 May 1965) is a Brazilian jazz and pop singer.
When she was eighteen years old, she worked as a backup singer for commercials and for pop stars in Brazil.
Koorax achieved some popularity in 1990 after one of her songs was played on a television soap opera.
In 2010, she performed 47 concerts in Brazil and 51 abroad, having toured Europe and Asia.
On tour in August 2010, she recorded Arirang Korean pop musicians and American jazz musicians  Lee Ritenour and  Alan Broadbent.

Her album Opus Classico (2013) contained works by Rachmaninoff, Chopin, Wagner, Debussy, Fauré, Ravel and Brazilian composers Heitor Villa-Lobos, Delza Agricola, Chiquinha Gonzaga and Machado de Assis.
In April 1990, Ithamara Koorax married fellow musician and producer Arnaldo de Souteiro.
